FBIS4-63921 "drsov102_d_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 Regional Affairs Kuril Islanders Want To Break Away From Sakhalin Region Kuril Islanders Want To Break Away From Sakhalin Region LD2505122194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1047 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505122194 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Residents of the South Kuril Islands frustrated over economic hardships now contemplate the possibility of breaking away from the Sakhalin Region, the strike committee of a large fish factory on Kunashir Island says. In a message to the Russian leadership, the committee has drawn attention to the factory's plight, run-away prices and endemic pay delays. It asked President Yeltsin to appoint his own representative to the Kurils.
